</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15user1650_008" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?></xref> 
<xref keyref="15_Clean_the_buffer_plate" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D9BA9B5E-765C-4069-BA28-E03D43FA8965.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Clean the buffer plate?>Clean the buffer plate</xref>
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check for the presence of 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">15-T-001 Buffer verification required</b> and do 
<xref keyref="SDS15-6-018" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-FCF3B250-0543-40FD-B0F2-511838FFF256.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15-6-018 Check buffer plate [Special Tests]?>15-6-018 Check buffer plate [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust the buffer plate 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="15ADJU004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-DCF00A51-9FFA-40C1-BEA7-097A8EFB8F9F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 15 How to check/adjust the buffer plate?>15 How to check/adjust the buffer plate</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Lower the vacuum settings 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">When loading media in the printer use both hands to move the media forward and slide it under the metal paper guide. When the media is handled on only one side there is a risk on skewed loading. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As pollution influences the friction of the buffer plate and therefor the media step performance, the buffer plate needs to be cleaned regularly by the customer (see Care &amp; Use poster). 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p "> When media step errors occur a white line can appear when the step error is too large. In case of overlapping steps a dark line will appear. The distance of the lines depends on the print mode. In high quality modes the distance is smaller than when speed modes are used. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case both dark and white lines appear in the same swath, this indicates the media step is uneven over the width of the media. As the X-tran rollers are only capable of an uniform transport of the media the cause of this artifact lays before the X-tran rollers : The buffer plate or skewed loaded media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The buffer is used to decouple the roll influence from the accurate X-tran during positioning the media. Pollution on buffer plate influences the friction of the media on this plate and therefor the effectiveness of the decoupling. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When the front of the media isn't loaded correctly the leading edge cannot be transported evenly. The buffer plate will correct this, but this can take up to a few meters depending on the amount of skewness. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
